1:1 COMMENT "# generator_chain.z -- composing generators via sequential"
1:59 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# for-loops in a single body."
2:30 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "#"
3:2 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# Two intrange iterators are concatenated by an outer generator"
4:64 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# `chained` that drives each in turn. The inline form"
5:54 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# `for x: (intrange ...) loop { yield x }` works because the"
6:61 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# desugarer auto-extracts a non-trivial for-loop iterable into a"
7:65 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# synthetic local before the loop -- the local crosses the"
8:59 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# enclosing generator's suspensions (yielding-loop rule) so it"
9:63 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# gets promoted to a field of `chained_iter` and persists across"
10:65 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# `.call` invocations."
11:23 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "#"
12:2 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# Equivalent explicit-binding form:"
13:36 EOL "\n"
14:1 COMMENT "#   inner1: (intrange lo: a_lo hi: a_hi)"
14:41 EOL "\n"
15:1 COMMENT "#   for x: inner1 loop { yield x }"
15:35 EOL "\n"
16:1 COMMENT "# (named local, same desugar outcome; the spec lists both forms.)"
16:66 EOL "\n"
17:1 EOL "\n"
